race.comment: The $160,000 Listed Members Cup closes out the card. TAVS (6) couldn't have been more impressive taking out the Listed Weetwood when resuming and is sure to have derived a stack of confidence from that dominant victory. Has won three from three over this course and distance and happy to have him on top in this contest. BATTLEFIELD (11) returned to the winners' stall at the latest outing and will be rock-hard fit for this fifth run in. Can go back-to-back. AMUR (7) goes well for jockey Thompson who has a win and a placing from two rides and has been racing very consistently of late. Genuine top-three conveyance. SPACE TRACKER (8) looks to be working up to another win placing in both runs this campaign and must be respected from the Archibald barn. In the mix. The very well-related WARBY (12) (half to G1 winner and stallion Captivant) next in line.
